content.description: Just a few feet to the left of route: Iron Curtain

content.protection: Bolts, quickdraws to a 2 bolt rappel anchor
content.location: Immediately right of Black Russian, starts atop a large boulder above a rather large drop.

climbs.name: Skating Away on the Thin Ice

content.description: Route has funky green lichen near the route. Starts off fun, gets pretty blank/balancy for 2-3 bolts. Then a rest-horizontal, and pull up and over a mini-roof.
content.location: To get to Skating Away/Cox's Climax, go another 50ft or so past Dano and King Kong, following the cliffline. Use the downhill trail for easier access or walk along the cliff face and hop down.

content.description: Route begins just left of: Brandenburg Gate
Crux is the top 10' as you scrape at the thin finger holds over a slightly overhanging bulge
content.location: 10' to the right of Dano (on the same starting ledge as Dano)

content.description:
Lowering chains are shared with route on climbers left Terror down that Wall.

 Easiest way to get to Ivan is to lower yourself between the two boulders (using the fixed rope if you want), then squeezing against the main wall to slip past the second boulder. This will spit you right at the bottom of Ivan.
content.protection: 8 bolts to chains, may want to stick clip the first bolt even though the start is mellow.

content.description: Begins just left of route: Pockets to Prague

The first 40' is very fun crack & face climbing (@this point near the bottom of a steep face) follow the obvious bolt line left towards a fun short cracked corner then onto a big ledge for a quick break. Your going to exit this camp ledge using a short dihedral with a lot of nice pockets to get you away from this ledge. Now just make a few more fun moves towards some tougher stuff. Crux is aprox. 75' up as you climb rather steep ledges with odd shaped pockets to assist
content.protection: Bolts to chains, bring a lot of draws
content.location: Shared start & first few bolts with 50' tall route on right named Dano

content.description: Crux begins around 40' up on a steep face with thin finger pockets & even thinner foot holds. Lowering chains for this route are @ the top of steep crux just below a large ledge.
content.location: The start of Dano & King Kong is up a nice 10' ramp towards the climbing to a camping ledge  approximately 30' to the right of Ivan the Democrat.

content.description: Approx 50' North (right) of Skating Away. Starts near a boulder and works up, and unto a rounded arete. Continues over a mini bulge to the top.
Shared chains with route on right: Black Russian
